Modifications applied by this project:
  1. Subset selection — only the structured control-metadata YAML files
     are redistributed. The control descriptions, audit procedures, and
     remediation prose in the upstream `benchmark/*.md` files are NOT
     reproduced here; consumers are directed to the upstream documentation
     URL embedded per-control in `controls.json` and in audit tool output.
  2. Format conversion — YAML files were parsed and emitted as a single
     JSON document (`controls.json`) for runtime consumption.
  3. The license, source, and pinned upstream commit SHA are embedded in
     a `_license` block at the top of `controls.json` so that any
     downstream copy of the data retains the required attribution.

The pinned upstream commit SHA and fetch date are recorded in `SBS_VERSION`
and in `controls.json#_license`.
